SR:
1. Create a class in a subpackage like this: 

```java
package subpackage;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}
```

2. Compile using the following command: 

```shell
ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java
```

3. Verify that the test.class file is placed in the subpackage directory.

4. Run the java command and ensure it executes without any errors.
